                Add to Cart
              




Tweet















              Description
            

              Reviews
            




Republic of Korea War Service Medal RibbonThe Republic of Korea (ROK) War Service Medal is a decoration presented by South Korea to recognize members of a military who served with South Korea during the Korean War from June 25, 1950 - July 27, 1953.  Personnel must have served 30 consecutive days or 60 non-consecutive days to be eligible for the award.










